<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-453-313  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 453 313.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Sept 3 1990 v20 n1p34(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development.andO;(Installations)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   MID Information Logistics Group (distribution).andO;Topic:     Desktop PublishingEquipment AcquisitionReport GeneratorsOrganization for Economic Cooperation and DevelopmentOffice Automation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The Organization for Economic Cooperation The Organization for EconomicCooperation and Development (OECD) in Paris has upgraded its publicationsfacility with the installation of Pager, the Vax/VMS-based, high-speed batchcomposition system supplied by MID Information Logistics Group, the UKdistributor for Datalogics.andP;  The OECD helps its 24 member countries toachieve economic growth and contribute to the world economy.andP;  Toward thisgoal, it produces reports and documentation that are made available fordistribution and sale.andP;  These publications contain a significant amount ofcomplex tabular and statistical material.andM;The order for 12 users represents the core of a system that eventually willbe available to the 700 authors within the organization.andP;  MID will use SGMLto get text from the DEC system to the Pager composition engines.andP;  It hasdeveloped links between Pager and the organization's mainframes.andM;Altogether, the OECD employs about 3,000 people and is one of the world'sprimary economic advisory organizations.andP;  It is also the largest user ofDEC's All-in-One system in France.andO;</TEXT></DOC>